AWS EC2 Deployment Guide

Stock Market Portfolio Management System

1. Launch EC2 Instance

Login to AWS Console.

Go to EC2 Dashboard.

Click Launch Instance.

Configure:

Name: stock-portfolio-server

AMI: Ubuntu Server 22.04 LTS

Instance Type: t2.micro (Free tier)

Key Pair: Create or select existing key

Security Group:

Allow SSH (22)

Allow HTTP (80)

Allow Custom TCP (3000, 8080)

Launch the instance.

2. Connect to EC2 Instance
ssh -i your-key.pem ubuntu@your-public-ip

Example:

ssh -i stock-key.pem ubuntu@13.233.xxx.xxx
3. Install Docker

Update system:

sudo apt update

Install Docker:

sudo apt install docker.io -y

Start Docker:

sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker

Verify:

docker --version
4. Install Docker Compose
sudo apt install docker-compose -y

Verify:

docker-compose --version
5. Pull Project from GitHub
git clone https://github.com/your-username/stock-portfolio-project.git

Go into project directory:

cd stock-portfolio-project
6. Pull Docker Images from Docker Hub
docker-compose pull
7. Run the Application
docker-compose up -d

This will start:

Frontend (Port 3000)

Backend API (Port 8080)

MySQL Database (Port 3306)

8. Access Application

Open browser:

http://YOUR_PUBLIC_IP:3000

Example:

http://13.233.xxx.xxx:3000
9. Check Running Containers
docker ps
10. Stop Application
docker-compose down